  - STATE_UPDATE: {'generated_prompt': 'Perfect! The prompt has been generated successfully. Now I need to output the content field from the return result as my final output, without adding any other text or explanations.\n\nThe content field contains the complete prompt for the Solver Agent. I\'ll output it exactly as is:\n\nYou are a premier expert in software testing. Fix the build for: xpdf.\n\n--- 【EXPERT KNOWLEDGE & STRATEGIC GUIDANCE】 ---\n**Expert Knowledge for OSS-Fuzz Build Failures**\n\n**General Principles:**\n1. **WORKDIR Conflict**: When OSS-Fuzz uses local checkouts, it mounts the project source at `/src`. If the Dockerfile sets `WORKDIR /src`, this creates a conflict because the system cannot mount the source over an existing directory that\'s being used as the working directory.\n\n2. **Dockerfile Best Practices for OSS-Fuzz**:\n   - Avoid setting `WORKDIR $SRC` or `WORKDIR /src` in Dockerfiles\n   - Use relative paths or let the build system handle directory navigation\n   - The OSS-Fuzz build system automatically sets up the correct working directory context\n\n3. **Common Patterns for Fixing WORKDIR Issues**:\n   - Remove or comment out `WORKDIR` directives that point to `/src`\n   - Change `WORKDIR` to a subdirectory (e.g., `WORKDIR /work` or `WORKDIR /tmp/build`)\n   - Use `cd` commands in the build script instead of relying on `WORKDIR`\n\n**Specific Pattern for Current Error:**\nThe error "Cannot use local checkout with WORKDIR: /src" indicates that the Dockerfile has `WORKDIR $SRC` or `WORKDIR /src`, which conflicts with OSS-Fuzz\'s local checkout mechanism. The fix is to remove or modify this line.\n\n**Recommended Fix Strategy:**\n1. Check the Dockerfile for `WORKDIR $SRC` or `WORKDIR /src`\n2. Remove or comment out this line\n3. Ensure build.sh uses explicit directory changes (`cd`) instead of relying on WORKDIR\n4. Test the build to ensure the compilation proceeds past the Docker configuration stage\n\n**Additional Context from Build Log:**\n- The Docker build completed successfully up to the WORKDIR directive\n- The error occurs after image export, when OSS-Fuzz tries to use the local checkout\n- This is a configuration/regression issue, not a compilation issue\n- The original error was a compilation error in fuzz_pdfload.cc, but we\'ve regressed to an earlier Docker configuration error\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 3] Fundamental environment misconfiguration persists: The /src/xmlsec directory contains libxslt source code instead of xmlsec source code. This is evidenced by: 1) The patch.diff is trying to patch xmlsec-specific files (src/openssl/kt_rsa.c) that don\'t exist in libxslt, 2) Previous attempts identified this same issue. The root cause appears to be metadata confusion: software_repo_url points to libxslt.git but the project expects xmlsec source. The Dockerfile clones xmlsec but the container mount overwrites it with libxslt. Need to fix the source code mismatch before attempting any patch fixes.\n- [Attempt 4] Progress made: The fundamental source code mismatch issue has been resolved. The xmlsec source is now correctly present in /src/xmlsec (configure.ac exists) and the target file src/openssl/kt_rsa.c exists. However, the patch application now fails because the patch doesn\'t apply cleanly to the current version of the file. This suggests the patch was created for a different version of xmlsec. The error changed from \'No such file or directory\' to \'patch does not apply\', indicating we\'ve moved past the environment misconfiguration issue to a version compatibility issue with the patch itself.\n- [Attempt 1] The build failed at Docker image creation stage with "Cannot use local checkout with WORKDIR: /src". This is a configuration issue where the OSS-Fuzz build system cannot mount the local project source when WORKDIR is set to /src. The original error was a compilation error in fuzz_pdfload.cc (displayPage function call mismatch), but now we have a regression to an earlier Docker configuration error. The issue appears to be with the OSS-Fuzz build system\'s interaction with the Dockerfile WORKDIR directive when using local checkouts.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2020 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:eb1da8283405680c0e1792f285f3c7574a58515cccb43e15e8788d565e3690e5\nRUN git clone  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/freetype/freetype\nRUN apt-get update\nRUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends -y make wget cmake qtbase5-dev libcups2-dev autoconf automake autotools-dev libtool\nRUN wget https://dl.xpdfreader.com/xpdf-latest.tar.gz\n\nWORKDIR $SRC\nCOPY fuzz_*.cc $SRC/\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\nCOPY fuzz_*.options $SRC/\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2020 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\n# Unpack the file and cd into it\ntar -zxf xpdf-latest.tar.gz\ndir_name=`tar -tzf xpdf-latest.tar.gz | head -1 | cut -f1 -d"/"`\ncd $dir_name\n\nPREFIX=$WORK/prefix\nmkdir -p $PREFIX\n\nexport PKG_CONFIG="`which pkg-config` --static"\nexport PKG_CONFIG_PATH=$PREFIX/lib/pkgconfig\nexport PATH=$PREFIX/bin:$PATH\npushd $SRC/freetype\n# Temporarily Add -D_GNU_SOURCE to CFLAGS to fix freetype\'s dependence on GNU\n# extensions for dlsym to dynamically load harfbuzz. This feature\n# should potentially be disabled instead of fixing the compilation.\n# See https://github.com/google/oss-fuzz/pull/13325 for more details.\nCFLAGS="$CFLAGS -D_GNU_SOURCE" ./autogen.sh\nCFLAGS="$CFLAGS -D_GNU_SOURCE" ./configure --prefix="$PREFIX" --disable-shared PKG_CONFIG_PATH="$PKG_CONFIG_PATH" --with-png=no --with-zlib=no\nCFLAGS="$CFLAGS -D_GNU_SOURCE" make -j$(nproc)\nCFLAGS="$CFLAGS -D_GNU_SOURCE" make install\npopd\n\n# Make minor change in the CMakeFiles file.\nsed -i \'s/#--- object files needed by XpdfWidget/add_library(testXpdfStatic STATIC $<TARGET_OBJECTS:xpdf_objs>)\\n#--- object files needed by XpdfWidget/\' ./xpdf/CMakeLists.txt\nsed -i \'s/#--- pdftops/add_library(testXpdfWidgetStatic STATIC $<TARGET_OBJECTS:xpdf_widget_objs>\\n $<TARGET_OBJECTS:splash_objs>\\n $<TARGET_OBJECTS:xpdf_objs>\\n ${FREETYPE_LIBRARY}\\n ${FREETYPE_OTHER_LIBS})\\n#--- pdftops/\' ./xpdf/CMakeLists.txt\n\n# Build the project\nmkdir build && cd build\nexport LD=$CXX\ncmake ../ -DCMAKE_C_FLAGS="$CFLAGS" -DCMAKE_CXX_FLAGS="$CXXFLAGS" \\\n  -DOPI_SUPPORT=ON -DSPLASH_CMYK=ON -DMULTITHREADED=ON \\\n  -DUSE_EXCEPTIONS=ON -DXPDFWIDGET_PRINTING=ON -DFREETYPE_DIR="$PREFIX"\nmake\n\n# Build fuzzers\nfor fuzzer in zxdoc pdfload JBIG2; do\n    cp ../../fuzz_$fuzzer.cc .\n    $CXX fuzz_$fuzzer.cc -o $OUT/fuzz_$fuzzer $CXXFLAGS $LIB_FUZZING_ENGINE \\\n      ./xpdf/l